Privacy Policy
FAQ
General business terms
Privacy policy of Navel GmbH & Co. KG, Kaffeeberg 10/1, 71634 Ludwigsburg, hereafter Navel.
Below, we will inform you about the nature, scope and purpose of the collection, storage and processing of personal data in the “
Mimics
” mobile game application. You can access this privacy statement at any time in the application under “Settings/privacy statement” as well as at “
http://privacy.mimicsgame.com
“.
By proceeding with installation, you consent to the privacy statement and the processing of your personal data, the details of which are described below. If you do not consent to the privacy statement, you will not be able to use our product.
Contents
Definitions of terms
How are data collected and for what purpose?
Which data are collected in connection with quality assurance?
Which data are collected when logging on/registering?
Which data does Navel process on its own servers?
Are data collected by the provider of the download platform?
Which party collects which data in connection with ads?
Can I have the data deleted and/or learn which data pertaining to my person are saved?
1. Definitions of terms
For this privacy statement:
Personal Data
constitutes all information, which refers to an identified or identifiable natural person
Processing
constitutes the collection, recording, organisation, storage, editing or modification, reading, accessing, use, disclosure by way of transfer, dissemination or any other form of allocation, comparison or association, restriction, deletion or destruction of personal data.
2. How are data collected and for what purpose?
In connection with downloading process, data are collected, saved and processed by the respective platform, that is, Apple ITunes, Google Play Store or the Microsoft Store. Navel has no influence on this form of data collection.
Furthermore, services of third-party providers are used to collect, save and process data. Naval only uses these data for the purposes of quality assurance, use as well as the further development of installed software and executing contracts.
Finally, Navel uses third-party services to the extent you use a software version that displays advertising for third-party products. These third-party providers place advertising from their customers in our product, which you use.
3. Which data are collected in connection with quality assurance?
Navel uses a software called Unity Analytics for this purpose. The software was developed by the company Unity Technologies, 795 Folsom Street, San Francisco, CA 94107 USA. We wish to refer to the following privacy policy:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
.
Unity Technologies processes data for the order of Navel in connection with the described purposes for statistical processing on the servers in the USA.
The following data are collected, saved and processed through Software Unity Analytics:
IP address of the user, data regarding user behaviour (in particular clicks, length of a session), game-relevant data such as the profile level, the XP (experience points) last login time and finally, the device model as well as the firmware version of the corresponding device. Furthermore, crash reports (programme line, incident, key data for the computer hardware used) are sent to us.
You consent to the processing of your data for the aforementioned purposes as well as to the transfer thereof to the USA for this purpose.
4. Which data are collected when logging on/registering?
(1)
You register with your Facebook account and have installed the Facebook app: As soon as you select this possibility by clicking the login button, you activate the Facebook app with all the approvals you have defined. Navel has no influence on these approvals. If necessary, you can adapt them to your needs and deny Facebook access to certain data. Based on this connection, Facebook provides the following data: the public profile (if present on Facebook, your first name, last name; the profile photo), list of friends. Navel does not pass any data on to Facebook. By linking the app to your Facebook profile, you are expressly agreeing to processing as well as the dissemination of data for the aforementioned purposes. Navel has no influence on data collection by Facebook. We wish to refer you to the following privacy policy:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy
.
(2)
You register with your Facebook account and have
NOT
installed the Facebook app: As soon as you select this possibility by clicking the login button, you activate the Facebook app with all the approvals you have defined. Navel have no influence on these approvals. if necessary, you can adapt them to your needs and deny Facebook access to certain data. Based on this connection, Facebook provides the following data: the public profile (if present on Facebook, your first name, last name; the profile photo), list of friends. Navel does not pass any data on to Facebook. By linking the app to your Facebook profile, you are expressly agreeing to processing as well as the dissemination of data for the aforementioned purposes. Navel has no influence on data collection by Facebook. We wish to refer you to the following privacy policy:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy
.
(3)
You register with your Google Account. With your Google Account login, Navel gains access to the profile information of your Google account for your personal authentication. The profile information, which Google provides in this respect includes: your name, e-mail addresses, an individual user ID as well as your profile photo if kept. Furthermore, Navel gains access to your contacts. Navel uses this information to link you and your contacts, who also use the “Mimics” app. Navel only saves your user ID on its own servers in order to identify you. By linking the app to your Google profile, you are expressly agreeing to the processing as well as the dissemination of data for the aforementioned purposes.
Navel has no influence on data collection by Google, we refer to you to the following privacy policy:
https://www.google.de/intl/de/policies/privacy/
(4)
You register with your e-mail address: Navel saves this e-mail address on its own servers. Your IP address, which is also located in the e-mail header, is also saved in this context.
(5)
Regardless of the type of registration, you give yourself a nickname in this step and can assign your own profile photo to your app account. All app users can find you in the app with your user name. Your profile photo will be shown there. You consent to Navel using, saving and passing on your profile photo for this purpose.
5. Which data does Navel process on its own servers?
Navel collects and/or saves the following data on its own servers to ensure proper use of the application so that the application can be used properly as well as in order to execute the contract.
Username + e-mail address AND/OR Facebook user ID AND/OR Google user ID depending on which login versions you use.
Device information
Push tokens to get news by means of push notification
Device ID, device type, OS version
Account status
IP address All data are transferred by the respective device to the services using SSL encryption.
6. Are data collected by the provider of the download platform?
The data are collected by the providers of the download platform in any case. Navel has neither any influence on nor is it able to access this data.
(1)
If you use an Apple product, data are also collected, saved and processed in connection with the download by Apple Inc., Infinite Loop, Cupertino, CA 95014, USA. Astragon has no influence on the data collected by Apple. Astragon refers to the following privacy statement: http://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/de- ww/.
