General business terms
Privacy policy of Navel GmbH & Co. KG, Kaffeeberg 10/1, 71634 Ludwigsburg, hereafter Navel.
Below, we will inform you about the nature, scope and purpose of the collection, storage and processing of personal data in the “
Mimics
” mobile game application. You can access this privacy statement at any time in the application under “Settings/privacy statement” as well as at “
http://privacy.mimicsgame.com
“.
By proceeding with installation, you consent to the privacy statement and the processing of your personal data, the details of which are described below. If you do not consent to the privacy statement, you will not be able to use our product.
Contents
Definitions of terms
How are data collected and for what purpose?
Which data are collected in connection with quality assurance?
Which data are collected when logging on/registering?
Which data does Navel process on its own servers?
Are data collected by the provider of the download platform?
Which party collects which data in connection with ads?
Can I have the data deleted and/or learn which data pertaining to my person are saved?
1. Definitions of terms
For this privacy statement:
Personal Data
constitutes all information, which refers to an identified or identifiable natural person
Processing
constitutes the collection, recording, organisation, storage, editing or modification, reading, accessing, use, disclosure by way of transfer, dissemination or any other form of allocation, comparison or association, restriction, deletion or destruction of personal data.
2. How are data collected and for what purpose?
In connection with downloading process, data are collected, saved and processed by the respective platform, that is, Apple ITunes, Google Play Store or the Microsoft Store. Navel has no influence on this form of data collection.
Furthermore, services of third-party providers are used to collect, save and process data. Naval only uses these data for the purposes of quality assurance, use as well as the further development of installed software and executing contracts.
Finally, Navel uses third-party services to the extent you use a software version that displays advertising for third-party products. These third-party providers place advertising from their customers in our product, which you use.
3. Which data are collected in connection with quality assurance?
Navel uses a software called Unity Analytics for this purpose. The software was developed by the company Unity Technologies, 795 Folsom Street, San Francisco, CA 94107 USA. We wish to refer to the following privacy policy:
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
.
Unity Technologies processes data for the order of Navel in connection with the described purposes for statistical processing on the servers in the USA.
The following data are collected, saved and processed through Software Unity Analytics:
IP address of the user, data regarding user behaviour (in particular clicks, length of a session), game-relevant data such as the profile level, the XP (experience points) last login time and finally, the device model as well as the firmware version of the corresponding device. Furthermore, crash reports (programme line, incident, key data for the computer hardware used) are sent to us.
You consent to the processing of your data for the aforementioned purposes as well as to the transfer thereof to the USA for this purpose.
4. Which data are collected when logging on/registering?
(1)
You register with your Facebook account and have installed the Facebook app: As soon as you select this possibility by clicking the login button, you activate the Facebook app with all the approvals you have defined. Navel has no influence on these approvals. If necessary, you can adapt them to your needs and deny Facebook access to certain data. Based on this connection, Facebook provides the following data: the public profile (if present on Facebook, your first name, last name; the profile photo), list of friends. Navel does not pass any data on to Facebook. By linking the app to your Facebook profile, you are expressly agreeing to processing as well as the dissemination of data for the aforementioned purposes. Navel has no influence on data collection by Facebook. We wish to refer you to the following privacy policy:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy
.
(2)
You register with your Facebook account and have
NOT
installed the Facebook app: As soon as you select this possibility by clicking the login button, you activate the Facebook app with all the approvals you have defined. Navel have no influence on these approvals. if necessary, you can adapt them to your needs and deny Facebook access to certain data. Based on this connection, Facebook provides the following data: the public profile (if present on Facebook, your first name, last name; the profile photo), list of friends. Navel does not pass any data on to Facebook. By linking the app to your Facebook profile, you are expressly agreeing to processing as well as the dissemination of data for the aforementioned purposes. Navel has no influence on data collection by Facebook. We wish to refer you to the following privacy policy:
https://www.facebook.com/about/privacy
.
(3)
You register with your Google Account. With your Google Account login, Navel gains access to the profile information of your Google account for your personal authentication. The profile information, which Google provides in this respect includes: your name, e-mail addresses, an individual user ID as well as your profile photo if kept. Furthermore, Navel gains access to your contacts. Navel uses this information to link you and your contacts, who also use the “Mimics” app. Navel only saves your user ID on its own servers in order to identify you. By linking the app to your Google profile, you are expressly agreeing to the processing as well as the dissemination of data for the aforementioned purposes.
Navel has no influence on data collection by Google, we refer to you to the following privacy policy:
https://www.google.de/intl/de/policies/privacy/
(4)
You register with your e-mail address: Navel saves this e-mail address on its own servers. Your IP address, which is also located in the e-mail header, is also saved in this context.
(5)
Regardless of the type of registration, you give yourself a nickname in this step and can assign your own profile photo to your app account. All app users can find you in the app with your user name. Your profile photo will be shown there. You consent to Navel using, saving and passing on your profile photo for this purpose.
5. Which data does Navel process on its own servers?
Navel collects and/or saves the following data on its own servers to ensure proper use of the application so that the application can be used properly as well as in order to execute the contract.
Username + e-mail address AND/OR Facebook user ID AND/OR Google user ID depending on which login versions you use.
Device information
Push tokens to get news by means of push notification
Device ID, device type, OS version
Account status
IP address All data are transferred by the respective device to the services using SSL encryption.
6. Are data collected by the provider of the download platform?
The data are collected by the providers of the download platform in any case. Navel has neither any influence on nor is it able to access this data.
(1)
If you use an Apple product, data are also collected, saved and processed in connection with the download by Apple Inc., Infinite Loop, Cupertino, CA 95014, USA. Astragon has no influence on the data collected by Apple. Astragon refers to the following privacy statement: http://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/de- ww/.
(2)
By using an Android device, data is collected, saved and processed by Google, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA in connection with the download. We wish to refer you to the
following privacy policy statement:
https://play.google.com/intl/de_de/about/play-terms.html
.
7. Which party collects which data in connection with ads?
(1)
Navel uses the Google service by the name of Admob to bill advertising. Admob is a subsidiary of Google, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. Admob collects, saves and processes data. Navel has no influence on data collection. We wish to refer to the privacy statement of the company
https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543
. You consent to the processing of your data for the aforementioned purposes as well as to the corresponding transfer thereof to the USA.
(2)
Navel uses the service of Unity-Ads, which belongs to the company Unity Technologies, 795 Folsom Street, San Francisco, CA 94107 USA for billing advertising. Unity-Ads collects, saves and processes data. Navel has no influence on data collection. We wish to refer to the privacy statement of the company
https://unity3d.com/legal/privacy-policy
. You consent to the processing of your data for the aforementioned purposes as well as to the corresponding transfer thereof to the USA.
(3)
Navel uses the service of the company Chartboost, 85 2nd Street,
Suite 100 L San Francisco, CA 94105 USA for billing ads Chartboost collects, saves and processes data. Navel has no influence on data collection. We wish to refer to the privacy statement of the company
https://answers.chartboost.com/hc/en-us/categories/200178116
. You consent to
the processing of your data for the aforementioned purposes as well as to the corresponding transfer thereof to the USA.
8. Can I have the data deleted and/or learn which data pertaining to my person are saved?
Yes. Granting your consent here is voluntary; you can revoke it any time with effect for the future. It can be revoked by means of a private Facebook message
sent to
https://www.facebook.com/NavelGames/
to verify that it is being revoked by the profile owner. At the same time, the profile of the user is irreversibly deleted. If you would like information about the data we have saved, please contact the e-mail address: support [@] mimicsgame.com or by post to: Navel GmbH & Co. KG, Kaffeeberg 10/1, 71634 Ludwigsburg.
FAQ
Why do you need Facebook-Access?
We need to uniquely identify you. Moreover we want you to be able to play with your Facebook friends. Mimics will never post without your permission on its own, nor do we access any additional privat content of you.
How long are my online pics saved?
Your online pic will, depending on how many party people are playing right now, be guessed one or more times. As soon as enough new pics are uploaded, the old one will automatically be deleted. This will roughly be something between one to seven days.
Where do you save my online pic?
We save the online pics on our specially for this developed server. Only two people have access – just for maintenance. All communication is encrypted.
I want to delete my account.
Just drop us a line with your connected Facebook account
here
or write us an
email
.
Can I support you?
Absolutely. All the time! Drop us a line anytime you want on our social channels!
General business terms
1. Domain of applicability
1.1 These General Terms of Use (hereinafter referred to as “Terms of Use”) apply to all contracts between Navel GmbH & Co. KG, Kaffeeberg 10/1, 71634 Ludwigsburg, Germany (hereinafter referred to as “Navel”) and the users of the “Mimics” game (hereinafter referred to as the “Players”).
1.2 Navel shall not accept divergent, additional general business terms of the Player, or those which conflict with these Terms of Use; they shall therefore not be included in this contract. This shall not apply if Navel has consented to the inclusion of the General Business Terms of the Player.
2. Subject matter of the Contract
2.1 Mimics is an online game available for download free of charge, which can be played on the basis of a profile on the social network “Facebook” operated by Facebook Inc.
2.2 To use Mimics, the player must have an Internet-ready mobile device with a camera.
3. Conclusion of a contract for playing the free game
3.1 In order to be able to play Mimics, the Player must register an account.
3.2 The Player shall select a player name and touch the “Register” button.
3.3 The Player shall access a registration form, which he or she can fill out by touching the “Open an account” button. By entering the data requested in the registration form and subsequently touching the “Register” button, the Player is submitted a binding offer to use Mimics. Before touching the “Register” button, the player may make any corrections to the information he or she has provided or delete his or her information or abort the registration process by closing the app.
3.4 Navel shall accept the offer of the Player with binding effect by activating the player account.
3.5 In activating the player account on the part of Navel, a binding contract shall be established between Navel and the Player for the free use of the Mimics game.
4. Conclusion of a contract for playing the paid game
4.1 The Player also has the possibility of registering for a paid premium Mimics account.
4.2 In order to register for a paid premium account, the Player must touch the button with the “shopping basket” symbol in his or her customer account.
4.3 The Player pushes the “Go Premium!” button.
4.4 The Player shall be directed to the shopping basket system of the respective app store. The contract shall be concluded between the player and the respective operator of the app store. Navel has no possibility of influencing the conclusion of the contract or the payment terms for the respective app store of the operator and in this respect, refers to the General Business Terms of the app store operator.
5. Publication of photos
5.1. Part of the game involves uploading photos, which can be viewed by third-party players during the course of the game.
5.2. Navel does not check the photos before they are published. If a notice advising of the illegality of a contribution is received, Navel shall expressly reserve the right to immediately delete individual photos.
5.3. The Player undertakes vis-à-vis Navel to not publish photos, which breach the laws of the Federal Republic of Germany or the rights of third parties.
5.4. The Player shall release Navel from all third-party rights, which are asserted vis-à-vis Navel on the basis of the publication of photos via Mimics. Unless the Player has consented to this, Navel shall not issue any acknowledgements or other legally binding declarations that establish the asserted claims of the third party.
5.5. The obligation to indemnify described under 5.4 of these Terms of Use shall be ruled out if the circumstances establishing the claims of the third party are demonstrably based on grossly negligent or intentional misconduct.
5.6. Navel undertakes to immediately notify the Player of the filing of complaints against Navel or the assertion of claims and to give it the possibility of taking over legal defence.
6. Warranty
6.1 Liability without fault for compensation of incipient defects in accordance with Section 536a (1) German Civil Code (BGB) is excluded.
6.2 Subject to 6.1 of these Terms of Use, the statutory warranty rights shall apply.
7. Termination
7.1 The Player may have his or her player account deleted at any time.
7.2 To do so, the Player shall send a request to deletion his or her account to the e-mail contact [@] navel.cc or it shall direct this request to the contact data provided in the game credits. Navel will delete the player account immediately upon receipt of the request to delete the Player’s account.
7.3 Subject to a request for deletion from the Player, Navel shall not be entitled to delete the account of the Player.
7.4 The right of both parties to extraordinary termination without notice shall remain unaffected. Navel shall, in particular, have an extraordinary right to terminate if the Player breaches the cardinal duties of the contract, in particular 5.3 of these Terms of Use.
7.5 Every termination must occur in written form.
8. Liability
8.1 Navel shall be liable in all cases of contractual and extra-contractual liability in the event of intent or gross negligence as prescribed by statutory provisions.
8.2 In other cases, Navel – to the extent not otherwise provided for in 8.3 of these Terms of Use – shall only be liable if a contractual duty is breached whose fulfilment makes the proper execution of the contract possible in the first place and whose fulfilment the Player may therefore regularly depend on (a so-called cardinal duty). In other cases, the liability of Navel is subject to the provision in 8.3 of these terms of use.
8.3 To the extent Navel is liable in accordance with 8.1 of these terms of use, this liability shall be limited to damages, which Navel has foreseen at the time the contract was concluded as a possible consequence of a breach of the contract or should have foreseen had it exercised the due diligence and care. Indirect damages and consequential damages, which are the result of defects in the performance of Navel, are furthermore only eligible for compensation to the extent such damages can be typically expected with proper use of the service.
8.4 Liability on the part of Navel for damages resulting from injury to life, limb or health and in accordance with the German Product Liability Act, shall remain unaffected by the above limitations and exclusions of liability.
9. Set-off, rights of retention and assignment
9.1 The Player shall only entitled to set off against legally established or undisputed claims vis-à-vis Navel. The same applies to the assertion of rights of retention.
9.2 The assignment of claims vis-à-vis Navel to third parties is only possible with the written consent of Navel. This particularly applies to the transfer of the player account to third parties.
10. Text form
10.1 Supplements and amendments to the agreements made between Navel and the Player including these Terms of Use must be made in writing in order to be valid.
10.2 With the exception of managing directors or authorised signatories, the employees of Navel are not entitled to make divergent verbal agreements.
11. Applicable law and jurisdiction
11.1 German law shall apply. The foregoing provisions regarding the governing law apply to consumers only to the extent that the protection granted by mandatory provisions of the country in which the consumer maintains its customary residence is not withdrawn (favourability principle).
11.2 The place of performance for all services in connection with the business relationships in place with Navel as well as the jurisdiction shall be the headquarters of Navel if the user is not a consumer, but a merchant, legal entity under public law or special fund under public law. The same applies if the Player does not have any qualification jurisdiction in Germany or the EU or its place of residence or a customary residence is not known at the time the action is brought. The authority to also appeal to another court of jurisdiction shall remain unaffected by this.
11.3 The provisions of the United Nations Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods shall expressly not apply.
